 :tx/rationale "PERF AUDIT FINDING P9-MAIN-DOUBLE-LOAD: main.rs opens a LiveStore TWICE per command invocation. Phase 1 (lines 108-131): opens LiveStore for session auto-detection, writes a session start transaction, drops it. Phase 3: opens ANOTHER LiveStore for post-command hooks (RFL-2 action prediction). Each LiveStore::open() deserializes the 92MB store.bin. This means every CLI invocation pays the deserialization cost twice. FIX: Open LiveStore once in main.rs, pass it through to the command dispatch. The session auto-detect and post-command hooks can use the same LiveStore handle. This requires threading the LiveStore through the command dispatch, which is a moderate refactor but eliminates a guaranteed 600ms overhead per command. Verification: only 1 LiveStore::open() call per CLI invocation (grep or debug logging). Performance: 300ms improvement per command. Traces to ADR-STORE-006, INV-STORE-021. Depends on nothing but benefits from P4 (daemon makes this irrelevant)."
